trans-unit.source: Add Hive libraries during HDInsight cluster creation | Azure
trans-unit.target: Add Hive libraries during HDInsight cluster creation | Azure

trans-unit.source: Learn how to add Hive libraries (jar files,) to an HDInsight cluster during cluster creation.
trans-unit.target: Learn how to add Hive libraries (jar files,) to an HDInsight cluster during cluster creation.

trans-unit.source: Add Hive libraries during HDInsight cluster creation
trans-unit.target: Add Hive libraries during HDInsight cluster creation

trans-unit.source: If you have libraries that you use frequently with Hive on HDInsight, this document contains information on using a Script Action to pre-load the libraries during cluster creation.
trans-unit.target: If you have libraries that you use frequently with Hive on HDInsight, this document contains information on using a Script Action to pre-load the libraries during cluster creation.

trans-unit.source: This makes the libraries globally available in Hive (no need to use [ADD JAR](https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/Hive/LanguageManual+Cli) to load them.)
trans-unit.target: This makes the libraries globally available in Hive (no need to use [ADD JAR](https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/Hive/LanguageManual+Cli) to load them.)

trans-unit.source: How it works
trans-unit.target: How it works

trans-unit.source: When creating a cluster, you can optionally specify a Script Action that runs a script on the cluster nodes while they are being created.
trans-unit.target: When creating a cluster, you can optionally specify a Script Action that runs a script on the cluster nodes while they are being created.

trans-unit.source: The script in this document accepts a single parameter, which is a WASB location that contains the libraries (stored as jar files,) that will be pre-loaded.
trans-unit.target: The script in this document accepts a single parameter, which is a WASB location that contains the libraries (stored as jar files,) that will be pre-loaded.

trans-unit.source: During cluster creation, the script enumerates the files, copies them to the `/usr/lib/customhivelibs/` directory on head and worker nodes, then adds them to the `hive.aux.jars.path` property in the `core-site.xml` file.
trans-unit.target: During cluster creation, the script enumerates the files, copies them to the `/usr/lib/customhivelibs/` directory on head and worker nodes, then adds them to the `hive.aux.jars.path` property in the `core-site.xml` file.

trans-unit.source: On Linux-based clusters, it also updates the `hive-env.sh` file with the location of the files.
trans-unit.target: On Linux-based clusters, it also updates the `hive-env.sh` file with the location of the files.

trans-unit.source: [AZURE.NOTE] Using the script actions in this article makes the libraries available in the following scenarios:
trans-unit.target: [AZURE.NOTE] Using the script actions in this article makes the libraries available in the following scenarios:

trans-unit.source: __Linux-based HDInsight__ - when using the __Hive command-line__, __WebHCat__ (Templeton,) and __HiveServer2__.
trans-unit.target: __Linux-based HDInsight__ - when using the __Hive command-line__, __WebHCat__ (Templeton,) and __HiveServer2__.

trans-unit.source: __Windows-based HDInsight__ - when using the __Hive command-line__ and __WebHCat__ (Templeton).
trans-unit.target: __Windows-based HDInsight__ - when using the __Hive command-line__ and __WebHCat__ (Templeton).

trans-unit.source: The script
trans-unit.target: The script

trans-unit.source: __Script location__
trans-unit.target: __Script location__

trans-unit.source: For __Linux-based clusters__: [https://hdiconfigactions.blob.core.windows.net/linuxsetupcustomhivelibsv01/setup-customhivelibs-v01.sh](https://hdiconfigactions.blob.core.windows.net/linuxsetupcustomhivelibsv01/setup-customhivelibs-v01.sh)
trans-unit.target: For __Linux-based clusters__: [https://hdiconfigactions.blob.core.windows.net/linuxsetupcustomhivelibsv01/setup-customhivelibs-v01.sh](https://hdiconfigactions.blob.core.windows.net/linuxsetupcustomhivelibsv01/setup-customhivelibs-v01.sh)

trans-unit.source: For __Windows-based clusters__: [https://hdiconfigactions.blob.core.windows.net/setupcustomhivelibsv01/setup-customhivelibs-v01.ps1](https://hdiconfigactions.blob.core.windows.net/setupcustomhivelibsv01/setup-customhivelibs-v01.ps1)
trans-unit.target: For __Windows-based clusters__: [https://hdiconfigactions.blob.core.windows.net/setupcustomhivelibsv01/setup-customhivelibs-v01.ps1](https://hdiconfigactions.blob.core.windows.net/setupcustomhivelibsv01/setup-customhivelibs-v01.ps1)

trans-unit.source: __Requirements__
trans-unit.target: __Requirements__

trans-unit.source: The scripts must be applied to both the __Head nodes__ and __Worker nodes__.
trans-unit.target: The scripts must be applied to both the __Head nodes__ and __Worker nodes__.

trans-unit.source: The jars you wish to install must be stored in Azure Blob Storage in a __single container__.
trans-unit.target: The jars you wish to install must be stored in Azure Blob Storage in a __single container__.

trans-unit.source: The storage account containing the library of jar files __must__ be linked to the HDInsight cluster during creation.
trans-unit.target: The storage account containing the library of jar files __must__ be linked to the HDInsight cluster during creation.

trans-unit.source: This can be accomplished in one of two ways:
trans-unit.target: This can be accomplished in one of two ways:

trans-unit.source: By being in a container on the default storage account for the cluster.
trans-unit.target: By being in a container on the default storage account for the cluster.

trans-unit.source: By being in a container on an linked storage container.
trans-unit.target: By being in a container on an linked storage container.

trans-unit.source: For example, in the portal you can use __Optional Configuration__, __Linked storage accounts__ to add additional storage.
trans-unit.target: For example, in the portal you can use __Optional Configuration__, __Linked storage accounts__ to add additional storage.

trans-unit.source: The WASB path to the container must be specified as a parameter to the Script Action.
trans-unit.target: The WASB path to the container must be specified as a parameter to the Script Action.

trans-unit.source: For example, if the jars are stored in a container named __libs__ on a storage account named __mystorage__, the parameter would be __wasb://libs@mystorage.blob.core.windows.net/__.
trans-unit.target: For example, if the jars are stored in a container named __libs__ on a storage account named __mystorage__, the parameter would be __wasb://libs@mystorage.blob.core.windows.net/__.

trans-unit.source: [AZURE.NOTE] This document assumes that you have already create a storage account, blob container, and uploaded the files to it.
trans-unit.target: [AZURE.NOTE] This document assumes that you have already create a storage account, blob container, and uploaded the files to it.

trans-unit.source: If you have not created a storage account, you can do this through the [Azure portal](https://portal.azure.com).
trans-unit.target: If you have not created a storage account, you can do this through the [Azure portal](https://portal.azure.com).

trans-unit.source: You can then use a utility such as [Azure Storage Explorer](http://storageexplorer.com/) to create a new container in the account and upload files to it.
trans-unit.target: You can then use a utility such as [Azure Storage Explorer](http://storageexplorer.com/) to create a new container in the account and upload files to it.

trans-unit.source: Create a cluster using the script
trans-unit.target: Create a cluster using the script

trans-unit.source: [AZURE.NOTE] The following steps create a new Linux-based HDInsight cluster.
trans-unit.target: [AZURE.NOTE] The following steps create a new Linux-based HDInsight cluster.

trans-unit.source: To create a new Windows-based cluster, select __Windows__ as the cluster OS when creating the cluster, and use the Windows (PowerShell) script instead of the bash script.
trans-unit.target: To create a new Windows-based cluster, select __Windows__ as the cluster OS when creating the cluster, and use the Windows (PowerShell) script instead of the bash script.

trans-unit.source: You can also use Azure PowerShell or the HDInsight .NET SDK to create a cluster using this script.
trans-unit.target: You can also use Azure PowerShell or the HDInsight .NET SDK to create a cluster using this script.

trans-unit.source: For more information on using these methods, see [Customize HDInsight clusters with Script Actions](hdinsight-hadoop-customize-cluster-linux.md).
trans-unit.target: For more information on using these methods, see [Customize HDInsight clusters with Script Actions](hdinsight-hadoop-customize-cluster-linux.md).

trans-unit.source: Start provisioning a cluster by using the steps in [Provision HDInsight clusters on Linux](hdinsight-hadoop-provision-linux-clusters.md#portal), but do not complete provisioning.
trans-unit.target: Start provisioning a cluster by using the steps in [Provision HDInsight clusters on Linux](hdinsight-hadoop-provision-linux-clusters.md#portal), but do not complete provisioning.

trans-unit.source: On the **Optional Configuration** blade, select **Script Actions**, and provide the information as shown below:
trans-unit.target: On the **Optional Configuration** blade, select **Script Actions**, and provide the information as shown below:

trans-unit.source: __NAME__: Enter a friendly name for the script action.
trans-unit.target: __NAME__: Enter a friendly name for the script action.

trans-unit.source: __SCRIPT URI__: https://hdiconfigactions.blob.core.windows.net/linuxsetupcustomhivelibsv01/setup-customhivelibs-v01.sh
trans-unit.target: __SCRIPT URI__: https://hdiconfigactions.blob.core.windows.net/linuxsetupcustomhivelibsv01/setup-customhivelibs-v01.sh

trans-unit.source: __HEAD__: Check this option
trans-unit.target: __HEAD__: Check this option

trans-unit.source: __WORKER__: Check this option.
trans-unit.target: __WORKER__: Check this option.

trans-unit.source: __ZOOKEEPER__: Leave this blank.
trans-unit.target: __ZOOKEEPER__: Leave this blank.

trans-unit.source: __PARAMETERS__: Enter the WASB address to the container and storage account that contains the jars.
trans-unit.target: __PARAMETERS__: Enter the WASB address to the container and storage account that contains the jars.

trans-unit.source: For example, __wasb://libs@mystorage.blob.core.windows.net/__.
trans-unit.target: For example, __wasb://libs@mystorage.blob.core.windows.net/__.

trans-unit.source: At the bottom of the **Script Actions**, use the **Select** button to save the configuration.
trans-unit.target: At the bottom of the **Script Actions**, use the **Select** button to save the configuration.

trans-unit.source: On the **Optional Configuration** blade, select __Linked Storage Accounts__ and select the __Add a storage key__ link.
trans-unit.target: On the **Optional Configuration** blade, select __Linked Storage Accounts__ and select the __Add a storage key__ link.

trans-unit.source: Select the storage account that contains the jars, and then use the __select__ buttons to save settings and return the __Optional Configuration__ blade.
trans-unit.target: Select the storage account that contains the jars, and then use the __select__ buttons to save settings and return the __Optional Configuration__ blade.

trans-unit.source: Use the **Select** button at the bottom of the **Optional Configuration** blade to save the optional configuration information.
trans-unit.target: Use the **Select** button at the bottom of the **Optional Configuration** blade to save the optional configuration information.

trans-unit.source: Continue provisioning the cluster as described in [Provision HDInsight clusters on Linux](hdinsight-hadoop-provision-linux-clusters.md#portal).
trans-unit.target: Continue provisioning the cluster as described in [Provision HDInsight clusters on Linux](hdinsight-hadoop-provision-linux-clusters.md#portal).

trans-unit.source: Once cluster creation finishes, you will be able to use the jars added through this script from Hive without having to use the `ADD JAR` statement.
trans-unit.target: Once cluster creation finishes, you will be able to use the jars added through this script from Hive without having to use the `ADD JAR` statement.
